parameters:
The old man's fighting tournament has
just ended, and now there's a war with
angels.

The source of conflict among old people
is something that never runs out.

\c[6]Old man\c[0] Huh?! What an indecent
outfit you're wearing!

Inn: Welcome, hello. The price for one
night here is 5 Rill, would you like to
stay?
Inn: We look forward to your next visit.

Inn: It seems you don't have enough
money...

Innkeeper: We have received a
reservation from Miss Mel.

Innkeeper: We have also received the
payment, so please rest assured.

Zerachiel: I'm tired today, should I
just rest now?

Innkeeper: Then, let me guide you to
your room.

Zerachiel: I hope I can have a good
dream.

Inn: Welcome, hello. The price for one
night here is 5 Rill, would you like to
stay?
Inn: We look forward to your next visit.

Inn: It seems you don't have enough
money...

Shopkeeper: The one handling the inn
reception is my daughter.

Shopkeeper: The one handling the inn
reception is my daughter.

Zerachiel: Ah, so you run it as a family
business.

Sachia: It seems like this building is
also owned by a parent and child.

Sachia: It seems like the knight order
is just renting the second floor.

Zerachiel: I thought it belonged to the
knight order...

Shopkeeper: Thank you, Rabi-chan, for
helping with the cleaning.

Rabi: If I could be of help, then that's
more than enough.

Rabi: Actually, I arrived at the inn
earlier than expected, so I was helping
the shopkeeper.

Shopkeeper: Oh, Claudia-chan... Alcohol
is prohibited, you know.

Shopkeeper: I heard from my daughter
that if you consume alcohol, you have a
tendency to undress, you know.

Shopkeeper: It seems there were no other
customers, but to avoid causing any
trouble, I'll have to prohibit serving.

Claudia: I know it's not a lie because
Sachia and the others always tell me,
but...

Shopkeeper: Oh, Guildmaster... It's been
a while, hasn't it?

Azel: Ahaha, long time no see. You seem
to be doing well.

Shopkeeper: Both the shop and my
daughter are safe.

Shopkeeper: ...The guildmaster is young
too, so don't push yourself too hard,
okay.
Azel: Yes, thank you very much.

Shop Owner: The number of customers has
decreased due to the war, but we will
continue to do our best.

Shop Owner: Thanks to all of you,
everyday life has returned. Thank you
very much.

Lulu: Oh, hello. Are you going to buy
something?
I want to modify my equipment

Lulu: Thank you for your patronage.
Please come again.
Lulu: Thank you for defeating Eden.

Lulu: I wish everything had been
resolved safely...
Zerachiel: Huh, what do you mean?

Lulu: Oh no, it's nothing. Please take
care of me from now on too.

Adventurer: Knights also use this
tavern.

Adventurer: Thanks to you, this tavern
is free from any conflicts.

Adventurer: Knights also use this
tavern.

Adventurer: Thanks to you, this tavern
is free from any conflicts.
Sachia: It takes courage to fight here.

Zerachiel: You could get caught if
you're not careful.

Adventurer: Knight Yuni-chan, she's
cute, isn't she?

Adventurer: I wonder if she has a
boyfriend...

Zerachiel: There's no doubt about it,
I'm in love.

Rabi: It seems that Yuni-dono is close
with a knight named Ishvald, they are
childhood friends.

Zerachiel: Ah, I've become so
despairing...

Adventurer: There's a knight named
Ishvald above us.

Adventurer: It seems like the captain
and vice-captain are absent, so she's
doing the miscellaneous tasks alone.

Zerachiel: I'm also borrowing Unie,
so... I feel kind of sorry.

Adventurer: Knights also use this
tavern.

Adventurer: Thanks to you, this tavern
is free from any conflicts.

Claudia: In my guild, even the knights
cause a big commotion when they come.

Claudia: It feels like someone is always
getting caught every day.

Adventurer: Knights also use this
tavern.

Adventurer: Thanks to you, this tavern
is free from any conflicts.

Azel: Actually, there are people who
cause trouble. I'll suppress them on the
spot.
Zerachiel: Oh no... what a disaster...

Adventurer: It seems that a war between
the Demon Lord's army and the angels
will begin as retaliation for the recent
attack.

Adventurer: I hope the Demon Lord-sama
does their best.

Adventurer: The Demon Lord is really
amazing, after all.

Adventurer: If things had gone wrong, I
wouldn't be able to drink alcohol like
this now.

Knight: The Demon Lord's legal wife is a
genius in swordsmanship.

Knight: But, the Demon Lord is
promiscuous. They had a big fight and
left after nearly killing the Demon
Lord.

Knight: Since then, the Demon Lord has
been heartbroken.

Knight: The Demon Lord's legal wife is a
genius in swordsmanship.

Knight: But you know, the Demon Lord is
quite promiscuous. They had a big fight
and left after nearly killing the Demon
Lord.

Knight: Since then, the Demon Lord has
been heartbroken.

Sachia: In every household, the wife is
the strongest, right?

Zerachiel: If we get married, we can
become the strongest too.

Knight: The Magic Continent is used for
exporting rare minerals and medicinal
herbs, among other materials, to other
countries.

Sachia: The unicorn horn and such are
valuable recovery items that can heal
the entire party.

Zerachiel: It might be a good idea to
buy a little.

Knight: There are rumors that the Angel
race does exist to some extent...

Knight: This is the first time I've seen
the real thing.

Lala: Hehe, worship me to your heart's
content.

Zerachiel: I shouldn't let it slip that
I'm actually an angel...

Knight: The Demon Lord has three
daughters, and it seems that one of them
is a master of martial arts.

Claudia: Mel also mentioned it. It seems
she has superhuman strength, just like
the Demon Lord.

Claudia: I want to believe that she
looks like her daughter.

Azel: Hey, good work. Are you taking a
break?

Knight: Yes, please rest assured that I
don't drink alcohol.

Azel: Thank you very much. After work,
please make sure to drink a lot, okay?
Knight: I will stay in the town.

Knight: Everyone, please take care of
the Demon Lord.
Knight: Shall I also do my best at work?

Knight: I want to become someone who can
protect others, just like all of you.

The residents: It seems that the Demon
Lord's daughter has returned.

Residents: It seems she was an
adventurer in the Empire.

The residents: It seems that the Demon
Lord's daughter has returned.

Residents: I heard she was an adventurer
in the Empire.

Sachia: Even if Mel is called a
princess, we used to play together so I
don't feel it.

Residents: Since spider-type monsters
use their threads to reduce their speed,
it's easier to defeat them first.

Zerachiel: Spider threads are sticky and
gross, aren't they?

Residents: Oh, there's a girl with
wings... Is she from the Birdman tribe?

Lala: I am an angel! Don't lump me
together with them!!

The residents: It seems that the Demon
Lord's daughter has returned.

Residents: It seems she was an
adventurer in the Empire.

Claudia: You're talking about Mel,
right?

Fishing Old Man: Do you know that you can fish in
the outskirts? I love fish, so I'll buy them at a
high price.
魚を買い取ってもらう

Fishing Old Man: Bring them to me if you catch
more. I'll buy as many as you can get.

serve you, young lady? I'll pay you 3000 ril."

31 or higher.

Resident: Miss, you're cute. How about serving me,
old man? I'll pay 3000 ril.

Zerachiel: (That's a lot of money, what should I
do?)
Zerachiel: I don't mind if you give me money.
Resident: Really? Let's go to the room right away.
Resident: Thank you for today. See you again.

Resident: Zerachiel-chan, hello. Will you serve me
today as well? I'll pay 3000 ril.

Resident: Thank you. Shall we head to the room
right away?

Resident: Thank you as always. I'll rely on you
again.

Resident: Thank you for today. Let's work together
again.
Zerachiel: Was that just a dream...?

Zerachiel: I had a strangely vivid
dream.

Zerachiel: (The Seventh Curse... Was it
also mentioned in Effy's diary?)

Zerachiel: (Wasn't it the leader of the
Orpheus Cult who was searching for it?)

Zerachiel: (I wonder if there's any
connection?)

Rabi: Yes, it's good to be in good
health!

Rabi: Today, we're going to the Magic
Ore Mountain to search for
\c[6]Adamantite Ore\c[0].

Rabi: Let's do our best together, shall
we!
Zerachiel: Yes, nice to meet you today.

Rabi: Let's head to the Magic Ore
Mountain once we're ready, shall we!
